original_conversation:
Speaker 1: Hi there, how's everything going with you?
Speaker 2: Hey! Things are going okay. Just trying to keep up with the hustle, you know. How about you? 
Speaker 1: I'm doing alright. Just trying to keep up with my studies. And the weather, so unpredictable lately, isn't it?
Speaker 2: Oh, absolutely! It's been so weird. One day it's sunny, the next it's raining cats and dogs. How's it affecting your campus life?
Speaker 1: It's been a bit of a struggle, to be honest. I have to carry an umbrella and sunglasses every day. But, I guess, that's life in Peabody, right? 
Speaker 2: Ha, indeed! You never know what you're going to get weather-wise. Speaking of struggles, how are your studies going? You're in your final year, aren't you?
Speaker 1: Yes, I am. It's been quite intense. There are so many projects and assignments to handle. But I'm trying to make the most out of it. And you, how's the consulting world treating you?
Speaker 2: Oh, it's been a roller coaster. Some days are packed with back-to-back client meetings, and other days I'm just buried in reports. But I love the challenge. 
Speaker 1: That sounds intense too. I've been considering consulting as a career option after I graduate. Do you think it's a good fit for someone fresh out of college?
Speaker 2: It can be, if you enjoy problem-solving and are comfortable with a fast-paced environment. Plus, being able to adapt and learn quickly is crucial. I could help you understand more if you'd like.
Speaker 1: That would be great! I'd love to get a better understanding of the industry before I make a decision.
Speaker 2: Absolutely, I'd be happy to help. Why don't we grab a coffee sometime and chat about it?
Speaker 1: Sounds like a plan! I'll get in touch with you soon to set a date. Thanks for offering to help, I really appreciate it.
Speaker 2: Of course! It's always good to help a neighbor out. Looking forward to our chat.
